units.name: CHG
units.description:
New universal charger.
2 agents: Charger, Accumulator

State flow:
- charger is in state NOT_READY
- after receiving beacon from an accumulator (`accumulator.state=READY`) + SDC_IN, charger is in state READY
- user presses Start button
- charger sets output voltage to `accumulator.CurrentVoltage + delta`, low current limit, closes SDC, goes into AWAITING_ACP state
- ACP precharges and goes into ACTIVE state
- charger goes ACTIVE, sets output voltage to TargetVoltage, current to ≤ ChargeCurrent and charging starts
- after ending condition is satisfied, charger dials down current, breaks SDC and goes into NOT_READY state
- when ACP recovers and goes back into READY, charger goes back READY as well and awaits further user input

enum_types.name: LVSupplyCapability
enum_types.description:
Indicates the accumulator's capability to deliver power to LV circuitry. When the acp is fully discharged, this enumeration will tell the FSB, what units are allowed to be kept alive. Right now units are divided by their importance into four groups matching four states with ascending severity. When the TS is deactivated due to very low voltage, there is no point in keeping powertrain alive. One step further, even cooling shall be deactivated. Hopefully the car does not reach the last state.

See https://eforce1.feld.cvut.cz/gitlab/fse08/ams-sw/-/issues/86 for some ideas. //TODO discus these options with the reset of ELS

items.name: FullyCapable
items.description: The accumulator is charged and can deliver sufficient power.

items.name: KillPowertrain
items.description: Voltage dropped below TS cutoff point. AMS won't engage AIRs again, hence units like VDCU, INS, DRS and MC are of no use.

items.name: KillCooling
items.description: Voltage is approaching critical level, any high power consumer should be disconnected (cooling and indicators).

items.name: KillAll
items.description: Voltage has dropped below the critical level. Kill everything that remains.

units.description:
Remote Emergency System

Zpravy posilane RESem popsane v FSG handbooku a dokumentaci, ktera prisla od vyrobce.

Node-ID se nastavuje na zelene krabicce a je mezi 0 a 63. Na zavodech musi byt nastaveno na 0x011, tak bylo rozhdonuto, ze to tak bude nastaveno porad.

Na zelene krabicce se taky nesmi zapomenout nastavit rychlost busu na 1000 kbit/s.

Michal Horacek (odstranena diakritika)
